      {
        "id": "d1961c15678e0ef95944bb44cd05b43cd0f1e307",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4341,
          "name": "Keong Lim",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
          "username": "keong"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-30 07:24:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n(4 comments)\n\nLooks like a nice re-factor, but the pay-off for 2 small public functions broken into 7 smaller private functions seems minimal. If the smaller functions were part of a public library, it might make more sense.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "fd8f9cbb4a09a0625eb5813703d80c6246851afc",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4341,
          "name": "Keong Lim",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
          "username": "keong"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-30 07:26:44.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nRegarding the test code, we don't need to test whether a particular class is registered, we need to test that a particular behaviour is implemented (there may be different ways to do the same thing).",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "b600ab68469c1a6602f8a05155a542bd45534562",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2731,
          "name": "KK",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "krzysztof.kurczewski@nokia.com",
          "username": "kurczews"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-30 08:26:54.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n(2 comments)\n\nAt first, thanks for your time.\n\n> Looks like a nice re-factor, but the pay-off for 2 small public functions broken into 7 smaller private functions seems minimal. If the smaller functions were part of a public library, it might make more sense.\n\nIn my experience short functions are better in long term. I can quickly understand them and once I got familiar with them I can mentally jump over them without loosing focus. I can't do that with large ones because context is bigger.\n\n> Regarding the test code, we don't need to test whether a particular class is registered, we need to test that a particular behaviour is implemented (there may be different ways to do the same thing).\n\nStill looking for nice way to test it.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "e4e7ac94fe5bdd2154207c74ddfd01838ba1e99f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4341,
          "name": "Keong Lim",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
          "username": "keong"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-12-03 03:26:01.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nAgree that it's difficult to know the best methods of testing.",
        "patchset_number": 5
